175
00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:34.100
your grandfather had already
begun making preparations!

176
00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:39.480
He devised a plan to poison
those irksome daimyo one by one!

177
00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:45.150
He got rid of them one after another,
making them all look like inside jobs!

178
00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:49.160
The series of daimyo deaths was
too much for the shogun,

179
00:07:49.160 --> 00:07:51.910
and he eventually took ill.

180
00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:54.660
His plan had been flawless!

181
00:07:54.660 --> 00:08:00.250
But just as he was within
reach of seizing power...

182
00:08:02.590 --> 00:08:04.960
that brat was born...!

183
00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:08.680
The heir, Kozuki Sukiyaki!

184
00:08:09.930 --> 00:08:11.220
– Yes!
– Yes!

185
00:08:11.220 --> 00:08:13.310
Congratulations!

186
00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:18.390
A curse on you, Sukiyaki!

187
00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:22.060
He was only one step away from power,

188
00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:26.240
and to make matters worse,
his plan was exposed!

189
00:08:26.240 --> 00:08:30.490
Your grandfather committed seppuku,
and the clan was removed from power!

190
00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:34.490
Their territory, castle,
and power were all taken away.

191
00:08:34.490 --> 00:08:37.000
People grew to despise the Kurozumi name,

192
00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:41.250
and the members of the clan
ended up on the streets!

193
00:08:41.250 --> 00:08:43.960
Whose fault could that be?!

194
00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:48.880
Who was it that made your life so miserable?!

195
00:08:48.880 --> 00:08:52.050
Who's responsible for your poverty?!

196
00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:54.930
Upon whom does the blame fall?!

197
00:08:56.890 --> 00:08:58.350
It's because he was birthed!

198
00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:02.100
Kozuki Sukiyaki!

199
00:09:02.480 --> 00:09:04.270
That's right!

200
00:09:04.270 --> 00:09:09.070
If he had never been born,
you would have one day become shogun!

201
00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:12.660
My lord, Shogun!

202
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:14.080
I love you!

203
00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:16.040
My lord, Shogun!

204
00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:17.500
I love you!

205
00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.920
My lord, Shogun!

206
00:09:18.500 --> 00:09:20.920
My lord, Shogun!

207
00:09:19.460 --> 00:09:20.920
My lord, Shogun!

208
00:09:22.170 --> 00:09:23.210
What beauties!

209
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:26.090
I'd have...

210
00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:27.670
become shogun?!

211
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:29.470
That's right!

212
00:09:29.470 --> 00:09:32.550
Oh, how aggravating! How galling!

213
00:09:33.340 --> 00:09:35.930
Don't tell me you're my...

214
00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:39.850
That is to say, a fellow Kurozumi?

215
00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:43.020
It doesn't matter who I am!

216
00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:46.190
I was out of the country all this time.

217
00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:48.400
It was quite the ordeal...

218
00:09:48.400 --> 00:09:51.320
But watch my face.

219
00:09:52.490 --> 00:09:53.240
What?!

220
00:09:54.780 --> 00:09:56.080
What?!

221
00:09:56.080 --> 00:09:57.740
Is that my face?!

222
00:10:01.160 --> 00:10:04.500
It's the power of the Clone-Clone Fruit.

223
00:10:06.210 --> 00:10:11.550
Should you follow my instructions,
I'm willing to bestow upon you a power of your own.

224
00:10:12.010 --> 00:10:14.720
You'll need this power
if you're to become shogun!

225
00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:18.100
I'll...! I'll do anything!

226
00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:23.940
Then begin hoarding money
and manufacturing weapons.

227
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:27.270
Wano's craftsmen are incredibly skilled!

228
00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:31.740
With them as bait, I'm sure
you can lure in some big-time backers!

229
00:10:33.150 --> 00:10:34.200
I understand!

230
00:10:48.090 --> 00:10:51.510
Hakumai

231
00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:51.510
My name is Orochi.

232
00:10:51.510 --> 00:10:54.340
My whole family has fallen ill,

233
00:10:54.340 --> 00:10:59.390
so I must find a way to feed all of them...

234
00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:02.270
That is most unfortunate.

235
00:11:02.270 --> 00:11:03.640
Work for me.

236
00:11:05.560 --> 00:11:07.940
A Month

Later

237
00:11:06.400 --> 00:11:07.940
Lord Yasuie!

238
00:11:07.940 --> 00:11:10.730
What? Orochi has disappeared?

239
00:11:10.730 --> 00:11:11.440
Yes, sir.

240
00:11:12.110 --> 00:11:15.740
And while it is likely just a coincidence,

241
00:11:15.740 --> 00:11:18.070
the money in the safe is gone, too.

242
00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:19.450
What?

243
00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:22.120
The money is gone, too?

244
00:11:23.250 --> 00:11:26.210
Kuri

245
00:11:26.210 --> 00:11:29.170
You are that fellow from Yasu's place...

246
00:11:29.170 --> 00:11:30.750
My name is Orochi!

247
00:11:31.170 --> 00:11:34.170
I owe Lord Yasuie so much,

248
00:11:34.170 --> 00:11:36.260
so I can't borrow money from him!

249
00:11:37.180 --> 00:11:39.390
I understand. You can count on me!

250
00:11:39.390 --> 00:11:41.680
You have my gratitude!

251
00:11:39.390 --> 00:11:40.600
Lord Oden?!

252
00:11:44.850 --> 00:11:46.390
Lend me money!

253
00:11:46.390 --> 00:11:47.440
Again?!

254
00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:47.480
Again?!

255
00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:47.520
Again?!

256
00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:47.560
Again?!

257
00:11:47.560 --> 00:11:47.600
Again?!

258
00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:47.650
Again?!

259
00:11:47.650 --> 00:11:47.690
Again?!

260
00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:50.020
Lend me money!

261
00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:51.150
Again?!

262
00:11:51.150 --> 00:11:51.190
Again?!

263
00:11:51.190 --> 00:11:51.230
Again?!

264
00:11:51.230 --> 00:11:51.270
Again?!

265
00:11:51.270 --> 00:11:51.320
Again?!

266
00:11:51.320 --> 00:11:51.360
Again?!

267
00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:51.400
Again?!

268
00:11:54.110 --> 00:11:56.240
Please lend me money!

269
00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:59.320
I can pay you back for sure this time!

270
00:11:59.320 --> 00:12:01.120
I'm begging you!

271
00:12:03.290 --> 00:12:05.000
Lord Oden...!

272
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:09.750
We are not doing well financially, either!

273
00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:12.290
He says he will pay it back!

274
00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:14.260
Flower

Capital

275
00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:18.970
Kozuki Sukiyaki

(Oden's Father)

Shogun of Wano

276
00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.470
Oden, why the sudden visit?

277
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:18.970
And without your retainers.

278
00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:21.600
Could you let this man stay here?

279
00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:24.600
He is a hard worker
and can even prepare medicine.

280
00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:26.850
He is like a younger brother to me.

281
00:12:27.310 --> 00:12:29.190
My name is Orochi.

282
00:12:32.060 --> 00:12:35.360
Everyone, please look after Orochi!

283
00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:37.650
Very well, my lord!

284
00:12:47.540 --> 00:12:50.040
Shogun Sukiyaki!

285
00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:53.210
I've finally made it this far!

286
00:12:54.300 --> 00:13:00.260
Back to

Where We

Started

287
00:13:05.890 --> 00:13:08.770
Lord Sukiyaki! Stay with us!

288
00:13:08.770 --> 00:13:10.140
Lord Sukiyaki!

289
00:13:10.140 --> 00:13:11.520
Lord Sukiyaki!

290
00:13:12.770 --> 00:13:15.480
Should anything befall me...

291
00:13:15.900 --> 00:13:17.610
I'm counting on you, Orochi!

292
00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.990
Of course, my lord!

293
00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:25.660
You, too, men.

294
00:13:25.660 --> 00:13:28.290
Lend Orochi your support.

295
00:13:28.290 --> 00:13:29.410
– My lord.
– My lord.

296
00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:30.410
Lord Sukiyaki!

297
00:13:30.410 --> 00:13:31.920
I-I'll go fetch a doctor!

298
00:13:31.920 --> 00:13:33.880
We'll be right back!

299
00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:35.590
Help! Is somebody there?!

300
00:13:35.590 --> 00:13:36.800
We need a doctor!

301
00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:38.170
Lord Sukiyaki!

302
00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.800
Are you all right, Lord Sukiyaki?!

303
00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:43.140
Take care of everything, Orochi!

304
00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:46.430
Stay strong, Lord Sukiyaki!

305
00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:57.650
You're gonna become shogun!

306
00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:04.780
Not long afterward,

307
00:14:04.780 --> 00:14:09.660
the news of Shogun Sukiyaki's
death spread throughout Wano.

308
00:14:21.550 --> 00:14:25.050
One day, in the fourth year
of Oden's voyage...

309
00:14:25.930 --> 00:14:27.510
What?!

310
00:14:28.640 --> 00:14:30.310
What's going on?!

311
00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:33.600
The fish are going crazy!

312
00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:36.480
Is some kinda natural disaster coming?!

313
00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:43.400
They are swimming away
from that island, Whitekichi!

314
00:14:44.070 --> 00:14:45.200
Yeah...

315
00:14:45.610 --> 00:14:48.370
Maybe some kind of monster lives there.

316
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:50.490
Marco, go take a look!

317
00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:52.830
No way! I don't wanna spoil the fun!

318
00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:02.090
Do not fret, Hiyori!

319
00:15:02.090 --> 00:15:04.050
It is nothing, Momonosuke!

320
00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:07.760
Should we check it out, Pops?

321
00:15:09.010 --> 00:15:10.260
Why not?

322
00:15:15.390 --> 00:15:16.600
Let's go ashore!

323
00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:18.940
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

324
00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:35.790
What? This is unreal!

325
00:15:35.790 --> 00:15:38.830
Are those savage animals running away?

326
00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:41.800
The must be something on the island...

327
00:15:47.630 --> 00:15:50.140
If you really wanna catch me,

328
00:15:50.140 --> 00:15:52.930
at least bring Garp or Sengoku.

329
00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:56.810
It's no fun fighting you lackeys!

330
00:15:58.480 --> 00:15:59.770
Captain!

331
00:16:00.270 --> 00:16:03.190
Whitebeard's ship just docked
on the opposite beach!

332
00:16:03.190 --> 00:16:05.740
Seems they've noticed us!

333
00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:08.990
We just wrapped up a fight, Roger.

334
00:16:09.910 --> 00:16:11.450
Whitebeard, huh?

335
00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:12.990
It's been a while.

336
00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:19.420
The birds seem distressed...

337
00:16:19.420 --> 00:16:20.750
They must've come ashore.

338
00:16:21.170 --> 00:16:22.630
Alright!

339
00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:24.800
Let's have at it!

340
00:16:24.800 --> 00:16:27.300
You can't fight once you're dead.

341
00:16:29.050 --> 00:16:31.760
And my time is almost up.

342
00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:36.930
This could be the last time
we ever meet, Whitebeard.

343
00:16:36.930 --> 00:16:38.230
Who's that?!

344
00:16:38.230 --> 00:16:40.270
He runs so fast!

345
00:16:40.270 --> 00:16:41.560
Is he a samurai?!

346
00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:43.110
A samurai?!

347
00:16:43.610 --> 00:16:44.980
The one I've heard about?!

348
00:16:47.110 --> 00:16:49.150
Quit lagging behind!

349
00:16:49.150 --> 00:16:51.410
Commander Oden! Wait!

350
00:16:51.410 --> 00:16:53.490
Shall I plunder their treasure?!

351
00:16:53.490 --> 00:16:56.080
This is a totally different situation!

352
00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:58.290
Don't mess with the Roger Pirates!

353
00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:01.080
He's not listening at all!

354
00:17:19.810 --> 00:17:22.600
Gun Modoki!

355
00:17:34.490 --> 00:17:36.620
He's as strong as they say.

356
00:17:36.620 --> 00:17:38.910
Should we stop him already, Rayleigh?

357
00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:40.000
Sounds like a plan!

358
00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:42.790
Wait, Gaban! Rayleigh!

359
00:17:42.790 --> 00:17:45.540
I can't have you two getting hurt!

360
00:17:47.590 --> 00:17:49.170
You just wanna fight him.

361
00:17:52.630 --> 00:17:54.550
I smell a beast!

362
00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:57.430
Hey, samurai!

363
00:18:00.060 --> 00:18:01.940
Divine Departure!

364
00:18:24.420 --> 00:18:27.170
What the hell was that?!

365
00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:33.090
Damn! I cannot let that one slide!

366
00:18:44.310 --> 00:18:45.520
There you are!

367
00:18:59.530 --> 00:19:01.120
They are not even touching!

368
00:19:16.900 --> 00:19:18.050
The ship!

369
00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:28.770
You look well...

370
00:19:28.770 --> 00:19:30.480
Roger!

371
00:19:30.480 --> 00:19:32.900
How long has it been...

372
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:36.070
Newgate?!

373
00:19:51.380 --> 00:19:53.510
– Drop your treasure and beat it!
– Drop your treasure and beat it!

374
00:19:53.510 --> 00:19:54.840
Give 'em hell!

375
00:19:56.010 --> 00:19:57.260
Rob 'em blind!

376
00:19:58.550 --> 00:20:01.470
The two great pirates of the age clashed!

377
00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:11.400
The Roger Pirates versus
the Whitebeard Pirates.

378
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:14.400
This fierce battle lasted
three days and three nights.

379
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:12.860
Second Day

380
00:20:18.070 --> 00:20:19.950
Don't underestimate me!

381
00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:25.330
I never underestimate my opponents,

382
00:20:25.330 --> 00:20:26.290
young man.

383
00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:38.720
Third Day

384
00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:57.070
Then, three boxes of dried meat for a barrel?!

385
00:20:54.520 --> 00:21:04.450
Fourth Day...

386
00:20:57.070 --> 00:20:58.200
Deal!

387
00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:00.990
I like this shirt! Where did you get it?!

388
00:21:00.990 --> 00:21:02.660
Let me have more!

389
00:21:02.660 --> 00:21:04.450
Wait! You took too much!

390
00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:07.040
It's all gotta even out!

391
00:21:07.660 --> 00:21:09.160
My bad.

392
00:21:09.160 --> 00:21:11.420
Maybe you can sweeten the deal?

393
00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:12.330
Yeah!

394
00:21:13.080 --> 00:21:16.510
From plundering to exchanging presents...

395
00:21:20.550 --> 00:21:22.800
Are they apprentices?

396
00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:24.930
Huh? Yeah.

397
00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:27.770
Now that you mention it,
they've been here the whole time.

398
00:21:28.230 --> 00:21:30.640
They don't look too tough...

399
00:21:31.690 --> 00:21:33.100
But they behave...

400
00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:35.610
like veterans.

401
00:21:36.360 --> 00:21:37.610
Hey!

402
00:21:37.610 --> 00:21:38.570
Shanks!

403
00:21:38.990 --> 00:21:40.030
What?

404
00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:44.410
You see the guy with the hat over there?

405
00:21:44.410 --> 00:21:45.200
Yeah.

406
00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:50.580
I heard he didn't sleep a wink
during the nightly ceasefires!

407
00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:52.540
Why not?

408
00:21:53.080 --> 00:21:54.080
Is he showing off?

409
00:21:54.080 --> 00:21:55.340
Not even close!

410
00:21:55.340 --> 00:21:59.460
They say, since the day he was born,
he's never slept! Not even once!

411
00:21:59.460 --> 00:22:02.220
Huh? Can such a person exist?

412
00:22:02.220 --> 00:22:04.090
Lucky guy.

413
00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:06.220
I wonder if his life is twice as fun!

414
00:22:06.220 --> 00:22:07.600
Idiot!

415
00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:09.720
It's not that simple!

416
00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:11.730
He must be a monster!

417
00:22:11.730 --> 00:22:13.310
A monster...?

418
00:22:15.440 --> 00:22:17.440
Hey, Oden!

419
00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:19.360
Can you really read it?!

420
00:22:19.730 --> 00:22:21.320
Indeed, I can.

421
00:22:21.320 --> 00:22:25.200
But why in the world
do you possess such writing?!

422
00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:31.250
Wano's Kozuki Clan has passed down knowledge
of this script to only one son per generation.

423
00:22:33.460 --> 00:22:35.790
It's already been thirteen years...

424
00:22:38.170 --> 00:22:43.170
We finally made it to Lodestar Island,
the last island that the log pose points to,

