636
00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:45.200
The government is telling us
not to go to the final island,

637
00:23:45.200 --> 00:23:47.530
which is said to contain treasure untold!

638
00:23:48.030 --> 00:23:50.660
That makes it all the more tantalizing!

639
00:23:50.990 --> 00:23:54.870
If we can reach it, we will be,
in both name and in deed...

640
00:23:54.870 --> 00:23:58.040
the world's greatest pirate crew!

641
00:24:03.630 --> 00:24:05.220
The world's greatest?

642
00:24:05.720 --> 00:24:07.300
That's right!

643
00:24:07.300 --> 00:24:10.100
And then, I'll...!

644
00:24:29.570 --> 00:24:31.910
I could not move.

645
00:24:31.910 --> 00:24:35.040
For the second time that day,
I was left speechless.

646
00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:37.120
Who exactly is this man?!

647
00:24:46.630 --> 00:24:49.010
What are you talking about, Roger?!

648
00:24:49.010 --> 00:24:50.970
That's a child's fantasy!

649
00:24:57.640 --> 00:25:00.350
I'm serious, Newgate!

650
00:25:01.060 --> 00:25:02.150
Please!

651
00:25:03.650 --> 00:25:05.400
I only need him for a year.

652
00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:07.740
Let me borrow Oden!

653
00:25:07.740 --> 00:25:09.860
This is my last request!

654
00:25:09.860 --> 00:25:13.700
With him, I'm sure I can get to the final island!

655
00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:18.080
Hey, maybe you should ask me first!

656
00:25:19.080 --> 00:25:21.710
Please, Newgate!

657
00:25:23.330 --> 00:25:24.920
I'm begging you!

658
00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:28.920
Hey, stop, Captain Roger! He's our enemy!

659
00:25:31.590 --> 00:25:33.850
Stop! That is beneath you!

660
00:25:33.850 --> 00:25:35.930
Do not bow your head!

661
00:25:36.350 --> 00:25:38.480
Please, Oden!

662
00:25:38.480 --> 00:25:42.350
Accompany us on our journey for just a year!

663
00:25:43.980 --> 00:25:45.940
Screw you!

664
00:25:48.900 --> 00:25:52.780
Roger! Are you trying to take
my family away from me?!

665
00:25:53.320 --> 00:25:56.240
But I could not help feeling excited!

666
00:25:57.200 --> 00:26:00.460
Why can the Kozuki Clan read the script?

667
00:26:01.540 --> 00:26:04.580
Why have our paths crossed?

668
00:26:12.300 --> 00:26:16.180
Before I knew it, the words
burst forth from my mouth!

669
00:26:17.510 --> 00:26:19.220
Whitekichi!

670
00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:20.850
I want to go with him!

671
00:26:21.270 --> 00:26:23.730
Please allow me to go!

672
00:26:23.730 --> 00:26:27.730
I wish to see this final island
he speaks of with my own eyes!

673
00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:33.360
You look annoyed!

674
00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:35.700
Of course I do!

675
00:26:36.030 --> 00:26:38.790
You're like a brother to me!

676
00:26:38.790 --> 00:26:41.040
It will only be a year, Whitekichi!

677
00:26:49.840 --> 00:26:51.210
Please!

678
00:26:56.010 --> 00:26:57.510
Take care of yourself!

679
00:26:57.510 --> 00:26:58.970
I will!

680
00:26:59.390 --> 00:27:01.390
We have decided to remain behind.

681
00:27:02.390 --> 00:27:04.140
We are fond of this ship.

682
00:27:04.140 --> 00:27:07.020
We await your return here.

683
00:27:12.650 --> 00:27:14.280
Sure thing.

684
00:27:14.280 --> 00:27:16.700
Men, you are fully-fledged pirates now!

685
00:27:17.950 --> 00:27:19.620
Let us all do as we please!

686
00:27:25.620 --> 00:27:28.960
Pops! Aren't you gonna send him off?

687
00:27:32.010 --> 00:27:35.220
Roger left us quite the thank-you gift.

688
00:27:35.220 --> 00:27:37.140
Tons of treasure!

689
00:27:37.140 --> 00:27:39.260
And look at all the grub!

690
00:27:39.720 --> 00:27:40.970
What?!

691
00:27:40.970 --> 00:27:43.310
You morons!

692
00:27:43.310 --> 00:27:46.060
Give the food back to them!

693
00:27:46.060 --> 00:27:51.440
I won't forgive them if they let
Kozuki Oden's family go hungry!

694
00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:53.070
Hurry up!

695
00:27:53.070 --> 00:27:54.280
Yes!

696
00:27:54.280 --> 00:27:55.860
Right away!

697
00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:02.540
Lord Oden!

698
00:28:06.080 --> 00:28:11.210
I will see you again, everyone!

699
00:28:11.920 --> 00:28:14.380
Give it your all!

700
00:28:15.010 --> 00:28:19.590
Can't wait to hear the story of your journey!

701
00:28:19.590 --> 00:28:21.970
Take care of yourselves!

702
00:28:32.730 --> 00:28:35.860
The second chapter of my
life as a pirate was starting.

703
00:28:36.360 --> 00:28:38.700
A new adventure was on the horizon!

704
00:28:39.200 --> 00:28:44.660
While Whitekichi is a great man,
Roger has an incalculable depth to him.

705
00:28:45.250 --> 00:28:47.500
Fortune has truly smiled upon me!

706
00:28:51.330 --> 00:28:54.550
Oh, good girl, good girl.

707
00:28:54.550 --> 00:28:56.630
Up, up!

708
00:28:57.760 --> 00:29:00.550
It's been so long since we last held a baby!

709
00:29:00.550 --> 00:29:01.800
Yeah.

710
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:03.720
It brings back memories.

711
00:29:04.260 --> 00:29:07.390
Momonosuke and Hiyori...

712
00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:12.400
Okay?

713
00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:14.190
Here we go! Boo!

714
00:29:20.150 --> 00:29:21.910
Captain Roger!

715
00:29:21.910 --> 00:29:23.280
We have stowaways!

716
00:29:26.290 --> 00:29:29.000
– Lord Oden!
– Lord Oden!

717
00:29:29.410 --> 00:29:30.670
Inuarashi!

718
00:29:30.670 --> 00:29:32.540
Nekomamushi!

719
00:29:34.460 --> 00:29:36.250
What are you doing here?!

720
00:29:36.250 --> 00:29:40.970
We enjoy your company meow than anyone's!

721
00:29:41.590 --> 00:29:43.970
The dog and the cat have vanished!

722
00:29:44.390 --> 00:29:47.770
Those morons...!

723
00:29:51.270 --> 00:29:55.860
Oden! You're only here because
the captain needs your expertise.

724
00:29:55.860 --> 00:29:57.320
Understood?

725
00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:02.610
Mock Town, Jaya

726
00:30:02.610 --> 00:30:05.160
Next, radishes!

727
00:30:05.160 --> 00:30:06.580
Thief!

728
00:30:06.580 --> 00:30:08.700
Captain's gonna kill him.

729
00:30:11.500 --> 00:30:14.420
Oden! Leave the civilians alone!

730
00:30:14.420 --> 00:30:16.790
I still need many more ingredients!

731
00:30:16.790 --> 00:30:18.050
Ingredients for what?!

732
00:30:24.430 --> 00:30:27.390
You've got some nerve!

733
00:30:29.850 --> 00:30:33.310
Huh?! Is this town actually lawless?!

734
00:30:33.310 --> 00:30:34.850
Gaban, they're...

735
00:30:34.850 --> 00:30:36.360
Yeah.

736
00:30:36.360 --> 00:30:38.400
Guess they're not civilians after all.

737
00:30:52.290 --> 00:30:53.250
Oden!

738
00:30:53.250 --> 00:30:54.870
He took it full-on!

739
00:30:56.880 --> 00:30:58.460
Oden!

740
00:31:13.100 --> 00:31:14.940
Oden! You...

741
00:31:15.770 --> 00:31:16.980
He's alive!

742
00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:18.150
Wow!

743
00:31:20.150 --> 00:31:23.530
Gaban, they're not civilians, right?

744
00:31:24.570 --> 00:31:26.030
No, they're not...

745
00:31:27.870 --> 00:31:28.910
Oden.

746
00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:30.490
Okay.

747
00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.120
I still need some kelp!

748
00:31:36.120 --> 00:31:37.630
Kelp?!

749
00:31:37.630 --> 00:31:39.420
It makes for a fine broth.

750
00:31:44.800 --> 00:31:46.050
You're so strange!

751
00:31:47.180 --> 00:31:49.760
Ah, screw it!

752
00:31:50.180 --> 00:31:51.680
Get 'em!

753
00:31:55.940 --> 00:31:57.650
– Oden!
– Oden!

754
00:31:58.020 --> 00:31:59.560
– Oden!
– Oden!

755
00:31:59.900 --> 00:32:01.820
– Oden!
– Oden!

756
00:32:01.820 --> 00:32:03.900
– Oden!
– Oden!

757
00:32:03.900 --> 00:32:06.740
♪ Oh, radish, ganmo! ♪

758
00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:10.620
♪ Chikuwa and eggs! ♪

759
00:32:12.080 --> 00:32:16.040
♪ One, two, three, go ahead and eat! ♪

760
00:32:16.040 --> 00:32:18.500
♪ Oden was meant... ♪

761
00:32:20.250 --> 00:32:23.460
♪ to boil! ♪

762
00:32:31.050 --> 00:32:32.850
Huh? Captain, did you catch a cold?

763
00:32:33.430 --> 00:32:36.020
Yeah, but it's nothing.

764
00:32:36.020 --> 00:32:38.310
It is something, you fool!

765
00:32:38.310 --> 00:32:40.980
He's only got a year to live at most!

766
00:32:40.980 --> 00:32:42.480
What?!

767
00:32:44.190 --> 00:32:47.320
I'm living life at top speed.

768
00:32:51.370 --> 00:32:54.370
It's coming... The Knock-Up Stream!

769
00:33:05.210 --> 00:33:06.590
I'm gonna die!

770
00:33:22.860 --> 00:33:23.980
An island!

771
00:33:27.150 --> 00:33:28.490
So that's...

772
00:33:33.820 --> 00:33:35.410
The sky island!

773
00:33:35.410 --> 00:33:38.450
Welcome, Blue Sea denizens.
You've traveled quite a ways.

774
00:33:39.540 --> 00:33:41.420
– Heso!
– Heso!

775
00:33:43.790 --> 00:33:46.750
The world is so vast!
There is no end to its wonders!

776
00:33:46.750 --> 00:33:51.340
Buddha himself could not have imagined
that people were living in the sky!

777
00:34:00.390 --> 00:34:03.770
It takes at least ten years to handle a waver.

778
00:34:12.490 --> 00:34:14.740
Run!

779
00:34:26.250 --> 00:34:29.170
So this is the City of Gold, Shandora!

780
00:34:29.170 --> 00:34:30.630
– Wow!
– Wow!

781
00:34:31.380 --> 00:34:33.470
I found it!

782
00:34:33.470 --> 00:34:35.090
It was all the way up here?!

783
00:34:41.480 --> 00:34:44.400
That must be the grand bell of Shandora!

784
00:34:44.400 --> 00:34:46.230
It's pure gold!

785
00:34:46.230 --> 00:34:48.570
Captain, how will we bring it back with us?

786
00:34:48.570 --> 00:34:50.530
I don't have time.

787
00:34:50.530 --> 00:34:54.530
Once you become a captain,
come get it yourself, Buggy.

788
00:34:54.530 --> 00:34:56.120
What?!

789
00:34:56.120 --> 00:34:58.240
We can at least grab a piece now!

790
00:34:58.240 --> 00:35:02.580
With such a strong voice,
this stone was easy to locate.

791
00:35:02.580 --> 00:35:04.920
It's talking about a great power, right?

792
00:35:14.340 --> 00:35:17.720
The text speaks of a weapon
by the name of Poseidon.

793
00:35:17.720 --> 00:35:18.720
I see...

794
00:35:20.390 --> 00:35:23.980
Oden, you can also write the script, right?!

795
00:35:23.980 --> 00:35:25.900
Yes, of course.

796
00:35:26.650 --> 00:35:28.020
Then carve this message!

797
00:35:37.070 --> 00:35:39.620
Roger is near the end of his life...

798
00:35:39.620 --> 00:35:43.500
It is difficult the fathom,
but if he is living with such urgency,

799
00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:45.830
I will follow him to the end!

800
00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:49.290
How is it?

801
00:35:50.590 --> 00:35:52.800
It's perfect, Oden!

802
00:35:53.630 --> 00:35:55.630
"I made it here.

803
00:35:55.630 --> 00:35:58.510
I will guide this text to the ends of the world.

804
00:35:58.510 --> 00:36:00.970
Pirate Gol D. Roger."

805
00:36:11.690 --> 00:36:14.150
I must see it, Roger.

806
00:36:14.150 --> 00:36:18.360
The final chapter of the great adventure
to which you have devoted your life!

807
00:36:26.580 --> 00:36:29.670
Men! Let's go back to the Blue Sea!

808
00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:31.460
– Yeah!
– Yeah!
